18/11/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- European Commissioner for External Relations Chris Patten says the EU supports the establishment of a single police structure in BiH.
Local media is reporting on Thursday (18 November) that Patten sent a letter to BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic earlier this week, reaffirming Brussels' support for the activities of the BiH Police Restructuring Commission.
Patten reportedly also emphasised that integrated police forces would increase efficiency and boost security for Europe.
In other news, Federation of BiH Prime Minister Ahmet Hadzipasic holds a cabinet meeting Thursday.
The goal is to overcome problems that surfaced recently among government partners.
(Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 18/11/04;
Fena, RTRS, AFP - 17/11/04)
